nestle.product.templates.NutritionTableTemplate='<div class="nutrition_table product_data_block"><tpl if="nutritionInformation.length == 0"><b>This product has no nutrition table.</b></tpl><table width="100%" height="100%" class="nutrition_table_header"">    <tpl for="nutritionInformation">        <tr><th colspan="2">Nutrients<sup><sup>\u2021</sup></sup></th><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel0}</th><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel1}</th><tpl if="numColumns == 3 || numColumns == 4"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel2}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 4"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel3}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 5"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel4}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 6"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel5}</th></tpl></tr>        <tpl for="items">        <tr class=\'{[xindex % 2 === 0 ? "nut_even" : "nut_odd"]}\'><tpl if="longValue == true ">            <td class="one" nowrap ><span class="feature_label">{label}</span></td>            <td class="two" style="width:5%" ><span class="feature_value">{unit}</span></td>           <td class="three" colspan="2" style="width:30%" align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value0}</span></td></tpl><tpl elseif="value1.length != 0">            <td class="one" nowrap ><span class="feature_label">{label}</span></td>            <td class="two" style="width:5%" ><span class="feature_value">{unit}</span></td>            <td class="three" style="width:30%" align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value0}</span></td>            <td class="four" style="width:20%" align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value1}</span></td></tpl><tpl elseif="value0.length == 0">            <td class="one" nowrap style="background-color: #09265D;background-image: -webkit-gradient(linear, 50% 0%, 50% 100%, color-stop(0%, #1BA0E1), color-stop(2%, #93D6F7), color-stop(100%, #1BA0E1)) !important;color:white;" ><span class="feature_label">{label}</span></td>            <td class="two" style="background-color: #09265D;width: 5%;background-image: -webkit-gradient(linear, 50% 0%, 50% 100%, color-stop(0%, #1BA0E1), color-stop(2%, #93D6F7), color-stop(100%, #1BA0E1)) !important;" ><span class="feature_value">{unit}</span></td>            <td class="three" style="background-color: #09265D;width:30%;background-image: -webkit-gradient(linear, 50% 0%, 50% 100%, color-stop(0%, #1BA0E1), color-stop(2%, #93D6F7), color-stop(100%, #1BA0E1)) !important;" align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value0}</span></td>           <td class="four" style="background-color: #09265D;width:20%;background-image: -webkit-gradient(linear, 50% 0%, 50% 100%, color-stop(0%, #1BA0E1), color-stop(2%, #93D6F7), color-stop(100%, #1BA0E1)) !important;" align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value1}</span></td></tpl><tpl if="parent.numColumns == 3 || parent.numColumns == 4"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value2}</span></td></tpl><tpl if="parent.numColumns == 3 || parent.numColumns == 4"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value3}</span></td></tpl> <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 5 || parent.numColumns == 6"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value4}</span></td></tpl> <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 6"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value5}</span></td></tpl>         </tr>        </tpl>    </tpl>    <tpl if="diabeticExchange">{diabeticExchange}</tpl></table><tpl if="nutritionInformation2"></div><br/><br/><div class="nutrition_table product_data_block"><table width="100%" height="100%" class="nutrition_table_header"">    <tpl for="nutritionInformation2">        <tr><th colspan="2">Nutrition Information</th><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel0}</th><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel1}</th><tpl if="numColumns == 3 || numColumns == 4"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel2}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 4"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel3}</th></tpl></tr>        <tpl for="items">        <tr class=\'{[xindex % 2 === 0 ? "nut_even" : "nut_odd"]}\'>            <td  ><span class="feature_label">{label}</span></td>            <td  ><span class="feature_value">{unit}</span></td>            <td  align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value0}</span></td>            <td  align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value1}</span></td>            <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 3"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value2}</span></td></tpl>            <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 4"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value3}</span></td></tpl>                     </tr>        </tpl>    </tpl>    <tpl if="diabeticExchange">{diabeticExchange}</tpl></table></tpl><tpl if="nutritionInformation3"></div><br/><br/><div class="nutrition_table product_data_block"><table width="100%" height="100%" class="nutrition_table_header"">    <tpl for="nutritionInformation3">        <tr><th colspan="2">Nutrition Information</th><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel0}</th><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel1}</th><tpl if="numColumns == 3 || numColumns == 4"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel2}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 4"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel3}</th></tpl></tr>        <tpl for="items">        <tr class=\'{[xindex % 2 === 0 ? "nut_even" : "nut_odd"]}\'>            <td  ><span class="feature_label">{label}</span></td>            <td  ><span class="feature_value">{unit}</span></td>            <td  align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value0}</span></td>            <td  align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value1}</span></td>            <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 3"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value2}</span></td></tpl>            <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 4"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value3}</span></td></tpl>                     </tr>        </tpl>    </tpl>    <tpl if="diabeticExchange">{diabeticExchange}</tpl></table></tpl><tpl if="nutritionFootnotes && nutritionFootnotes.length"><br/><ul class=nut_notes><tpl for="nutritionFootnotes"><li>{.}</li></tpl></ul></tpl></div>';
nestle.product.templates.AminoAcidTableTemplate='<div class="nutrition_table product_data_block"><tpl if="aminoAcidTable.length == 0"><b>This product has no amino table.</b></tpl><table width="100%" height="100%" class="nutrition_table_header"">    <tpl for="aminoAcidTable">        <tr><th colspan="2"style="width:46%;">Amino Acid</th><th class="nut_header" style="padding-right: 3px;">{columnKcal}</th><th class="nut_header" style="padding-right: 3px;">{columnG}</th><tpl if="numColumns == 3 || numColumns == 4"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel2}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 4"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel3}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 5"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel4}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 6"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel5}</th></tpl></tr>        <tpl for="items">        <tr class=\'{[xindex % 2 === 0 ? "nut_even" : "nut_odd"]}\'>            <td  ><span class="feature_label" style="font-weight: bold;">{name}</span></td>            <td  ><span class="feature_value" style="font-weight: bold;">{unit}</span></td>            <td  align="right"><span class="feature_values" >{valueKcal}</span></td>            <td  align="right"><span class="feature_values">{valueG}</span></td>            <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 3 || parent.numColumns == 4"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value2}</span></td></tpl><tpl if="parent.numColumns == 3 || parent.numColumns == 4"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value3}</span></td></tpl> <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 5 || parent.numColumns == 6"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value4}</span></td></tpl> <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 6"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value5}</span></td></tpl>         </tr>        </tpl>    </tpl>    <tpl if="diabeticExchange">{diabeticExchange}</tpl></table><tpl if="aminoAcidFootnotes && aminoAcidFootnotes.length"><br/><ul class=nut_notes><tpl for="aminoAcidFootnotes"><li>{.}</li></tpl></ul></tpl><br><br><tpl if="fattyAcidTable.length == 0"><b>This product has no fatty acid table.</b></tpl><table width="100%" height="100%" class="nutrition_table_header"">    <tpl for="fattyAcidTable">        <tr><th colspan="2" style="width: 46%;">Fatty Acid</th><th class="nut_header" style="padding-right: 3px;">{columnKcal}</th><th class="nut_header" style="padding-right: 3px;">{columnG}</th><tpl if="numColumns == 3 || numColumns == 4"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel2}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 4"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel3}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 5"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel4}</th></tpl><tpl if="numColumns == 6"><th class="nut_header">{columnLabel5}</th></tpl></tr>        <tpl for="items">        <tr class=\'{[xindex % 2 === 0 ? "nut_even" : "nut_odd"]}\'><tpl if="name === \'Total Saturated Acids\' || name === \'Total Monounsaturated Acids\' || name === \'Total Polyunsaturated Acids\' ">            <td  ><span class="feature_label" style="font-weight: bold;">{name}</span></td>            <td  ><span class="feature_value" style="font-weight: bold;">{unit}</span></td>            <td  align="right"><span class="feature_values" style="font-weight: bold;">{valueKcal}</span></td>            <td  align="right"><span class="feature_values" style="font-weight: bold;">{valueG}</span></td></tpl><tpl elseif="name != \'Total Saturated Acids\' && name != \'Total Monounsaturated Acids\' && name != \'Total Polyunsaturated Acids\' ">            <td  ><span class="feature_label">{name}</span></td>            <td  ><span class="feature_value">{unit}</span></td>            <td  align="right"><span class="feature_values" >{valueKcal}</span></td>            <td  align="right"><span class="feature_values" >{valueG}</span></td></tpl>            <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 3 || parent.numColumns == 4"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value2}</span></td></tpl><tpl if="parent.numColumns == 3 || parent.numColumns == 4"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value3}</span></td></tpl> <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 5 || parent.numColumns == 6"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value4}</span></td></tpl> <tpl if="parent.numColumns == 6"><td align="right"><span class="feature_value">{value5}</span></td></tpl>         </tr>        </tpl>    </tpl>    <tpl if="diabeticExchange">{diabeticExchange}</tpl></table><tpl if="fattyAcidFootnotes && fattyAcidFootnotes.length"><br/><ul class=nut_notes><tpl for="fattyAcidFootnotes"><li>{.}</li></tpl></ul></tpl></div>';
nestle.product.templates.OrderingTemplate='<div class="order_container product_data_block"><h1 class="order_title">Ordering Information</h1><table class="order_table">    <tpl for="orderTypes">        <tpl if="headers">            <tr class="order_header">                <tpl for="headers">                    <td>{.}</td>                </tpl>            </tr>        </tpl>        <tpl if="!headers">            <tr>                <td class="order_sub_header" colspan="4"><span>{type}</span></td>            </tr>        </tpl>        <tpl for="rows">            <tr class="order_row">                <td>{type}</td>                <tpl if="prodCode"><td>{prodCode}</td></tpl>                <tpl if="frSize"><td>{frSize}</td></tpl>                <tpl if="ndc"><td>{ndc}</td></tpl>                <tpl if="upc"><td>{upc}</td></tpl>                <tpl if="packaging"><td>{packaging}</td></tpl>                <tpl if="size"><td>{size}</td></tpl>                <tpl if="description"><td>{description}</td></tpl>                <tpl if="servings"><td>{servings}</td></tpl>                <tpl if="valveColor"><td>{valveColor}</td></tpl>                <tpl if="balloonSize"><td>{balloonSize}</td></tpl>                <tpl if="qty"><td>{qty}</td></tpl>            </tr>        </tpl>    </tpl></table><tpl if="footnotes && footnotes.length"><br/><br/><ul class=nut_notes><tpl for="footnotes"><li>{.}</li></tpl></ul></tpl></div>';
nestle.product.templates.DescriptionsTemplate='<tpl for="descriptions">   <h1 class="product_description"><span>{.}</span></h1></tpl><tpl if="footnotes && footnotes.length"><br/><br/><ul class=nut_notes><tpl for="footnotes"><li>{.}</li></tpl></ul></tpl>';nestle.product.templates.TypeTemplate='<h1 class="product_title" style="padding-right: 25px;">{name}</h1><h1 class="product_type">{category}</h1>';nestle.product.templates.LandingPage='<img width="732" src="images/ic.png"/>';
nestle.product.templates.CoverTemplate='<div class="cover"></div>';nestle.product.templates.PhoneCoverTemplate='<div class="phone_cover"></div>';nestle.product.templates.LandingTemplate='<div class=landing_html>    <div>\t<h1>Welcome to the GERBER<sup>&reg;</sup> GOOD START<sup>&reg;</sup> Formula Guide App</h1> \t<p> GERBER<sup>&reg;</sup> GOOD START<sup>&reg;</sup> offers a range of milk-based and soy-based routine infant formulas for babies from birth to 12 months of age with unique functional benefits. <br><p>All of our milk-based products are made with 100% whey protein partially hydrolyzed for easy digestion. Our soy-based products are routine infant formulas made with 100% soy protein partially hydrolyzed. All of our products have DHA & ARA to support visual and cognitive development. <br>\t</p><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="images/prodfam_home.png" /></div>\t</div>    <div class=landing_left style="width:100%">All GERBER<sup>&reg;</sup> infant formulas meet the high nutritional standards recommended by the American Academy of Pediatrics Committee on Nutrition (AAP/CON) and required by the Food and Drug Administration (FDA), in addition to our own strict standards. <br>   </p><div style="text-align: center"><img src="images/qcbutton.png" /> </div><br> \t<p>Data on all GERBER<sup>&reg;</sup> infant formulations as of October 2012. Information is subject to change. Please read the product label on package for the most up-to-date nutrient information.</p><br><img src="images/taglogo.png" style="float: right"/> </div>\t<div class=landing_right>\t</div>\t<div class=landing_right>\t<div class=clear></div>   <div id="manualButton"></div>\t</div>\t<div class=clear></div><div class="references"></div>';
nestle.product.templates.ToolsLandingTemplate='<div class=landing_html>    <div>\t<h1>GERBER<sup>&reg;</sup> GOOD START<sup>&reg;</sup> Nutrition Tools and Guides</h1> \t<p>      Guides for medical professionals on preparing alternate dilutions of GOOD START<sup>&reg;</sup> Gentle, GOOD START<sup>&reg;</sup> Protect, GOOD START<sup>&reg;</sup> Soothe, GOOD START<sup>&reg;</sup> Soy, and GOOD START<sup>&reg;</sup> Premature 24 infant formulas, including nutrient profiles of the standard and higher calorie concentration preparations.<br><p>Convenient guides to Gram Weights, Displacement Factors, Scoop Size, and Nutrient Values for GERBER<sup>&reg;</sup> GOOD START<sup>&reg;</sup> infant formula powders are also provided. <br></p><p>For more information on GERBER<sup>&reg;</sup> GOOD START<sup>&reg;</sup> infant formulas, or to print Recipes and Nutrient Data for calorie Modification or Nutrient Data on Powdered Infant Formulas, please visit medical.gerber.com.\t</p>\t</div>    <div class=landing_left style="width:100%">\t<div class=landing_right>\t</div>\t<div class=landing_right>\t<div class=clear></div>   <div id="manualButton"></div>\t</div>\t<div class=clear></div><div class="references"></div>';
nestle.product.templates.ManualTemplate='<div class=landing_html><h1>Nestle HealthCare Nutrition Product Guide Manual</h1><p><b>The guide is compatible with the following devices, browsers, and operating systems:</b><p><table border="0" align="center" cellspacing=0><tr><td>Apple iPhone</td><td>3GS, 4</td><td>4.2.x+</td></tr><tr><td>Apple iPad</td><td>1 & 2</td><td> 4.2.x+</td></tr><tr><td>Android</td><td>Smartphone</td><td>2.2.x+</td></tr><tr><td>Android</td><td>Tablet</td><td>3.x+</td></tr><tr><td>Chrome</td><td>Windows & Mac OS X</td><td>12.x.+</td></tr><td>Safari</td><td>Windows & Mac OS X</td><td>5.x+</td></table><br><p>(Please see the additional <a href="#compatibility">compatibility documentation</a> for instructions on how to check to see if your device or browser is compatible with the online guide.)<br><p>To launch the guide on any supported device or browser, simply invoke the URL http://productguide.nestle-nutrition.com, once the guide downloads it will be ready for use.  (Please note that the speed in which the Guide Application loads is dependent on network speeds and conditions, which may vary depending on your carrier and location.)<br><p>Please note, that for all versions of the guide, you will need to accept the Terms and Conditions of the guide to use it, and once accepted, you will not be prompted again.<p><img src="images/tc_tab.PNG" width="50%"/><img src="images/tc_phone.PNG" width="25%"/><p><b>Desktop / Tablet Version Instructions:</b><p>Upon launch, after accepting the Terms & Conditions upon your first visit, you will see the following HOME screen.<p><img src="images/tab1.PNG" width="50%"/><p>You can visit the various Nestl\u00e9 support sites by tapping on the various links to leave the Guide Application and visit either Facebook, or other Nestl\u00e9 support sites.  Additional information about the guide is available by scrolling down by holding your finger or mouse on the screen and moving the screen up.  You can return to this screen at any time by tapping the HOME icon in the upper right hand corner of the title bar at the top of the guide.<p>From this screen, you can tap or click and scroll the INDEX on the left hand side to find a product by name.  The INDEX is alphabetical order and you can use the convenient ALPHABETICAL INDEX on the right side of the INDEX to quickly jump to the letter category you are looking for.  <p><img src="images/tab_refs_btn.png" width="50%"/><p>On the upper right hand corner next to the Home icon is a button labeled "References".  You can tap this at any time to visit the References section of the Guide.<p><img src="images/tab_refs.png" width="50%"/><p>Once you have toggled the References Section, you can return to the Product Index at any time by tapping the HOME icon.<p>You can also SORT the products by tapping on the CATEGORY list above the BRAND SEARCH field at the top right of the Guide.  A CATEGORY LIST will appear and by selecting a main category or subcategory you can refine the INDEX to show just the qualifying products. <p><img src="images/tab2.PNG" width="50%"/><p>To reset the INDEX, please select \u201cShow All Products\u201d from the top of the CATEGORIES list.  Further, when in the \u201cShow All Products\u201d view, you can refine the INDEX by typing in the first letters of a Product BRAND name, such as \u201cBoo\u201d for \u201cBoost\u201d branded products as shown below.  You can reset the BRAND SEARCH by tapping the field and entering a new search or clearing the current search.<p><img src="images/tab3.PNG" width="50%"/><p>By tapping on the arrow or name of any product name in the list you can view the PRODUCT overview in the ABOUT Tab, as displayed in the image below which shows \u201cBoost Plus (Retail\u201d).  <p><img src="images/tab4.PNG" width="50%"/><p>From the ABOUT view, you will see the highlights at a glance about this product, such as FEATURES, NUTRITION FEATURES, and APPROPRIATE USES.  If you wish to quickly recommend or forward this product to an interested party, you can tap or click on the RECOMMEND PRODUCT button in the top left of the title bar to invoke your locally installed email client as shown below.  This function is not available for all products and you must be on the ABOUT tab to use the email product feature.  (Please note, you must have a working and configured email client set up on your desktop or device, if you do not you will have to configure this or have it configured prior to using this feature.)<p><img src="images/tab5.PNG" width="50%"/><p>If you wish to see more detailed information about the PRODUCT, you can tap on the tabs of the other segments for the product, such as FEATURES AND USES, INGREDIENTS, NUTRITION INFORMATION, and ORDERING INFO as shown in different images below.  Each one of these tab views contains the detailed information in accordance with the title of the view.  The view can be scrolled up and down as necessary to view the entire list of information.<p><img src="images/tab6.PNG" width="50%"/><p><img src="images/tab7.PNG" width="50%"/><p><img src="images/tab8.PNG" width="50%"/><p><img src="images/tab9.PNG" width="50%"/><p>When you are inside the ORDERING INFO view of any Product, you will find the ADDITIONAL ORDERING INFO button.  By tapping or clicking on this button, you will see a view that contains all additional reference information for the products contained in this Guide shown below.  To exit this view, simply press the \u2018Back\u2019 button.  You can also navigate to any Product in the guide, or return to the HOME screen from this view as well.<p><img src="images/tab10.PNG" width="50%"/><p>At any point when using the Guide, you can create a \u2018Web Clip\u2019 or favorite that will add the page to your device home screen when using an Apple iOS device.   To do so, simple press the ADD BOOKMARK icon found in the Apple Safari Browser.  Select the \u2018Add to Home Screen\u2019 option as shown in below. <p><img src="images/tab11.PNG" width="50%"/><p>You will be asked to confirm this action, in which you can rename the Guide if you choose, otherwise press \u2018Add\u2019 (as shown below) and you will leave the browser and a shortcut will be placed on your Apple iOS device\u2019 home screen.  You can tap the Apple Safari icon to return to the guide, or use the \u2018Web Clip\u2019 shortcut to return to the Guide, but when using the shortcut, the browser will be dedicated to the Guide.  Please be patient when reloading the guide, as the Guide must update to ensure the latest information is present.<p><img src="images/tab12.PNG" width="50%"/><p><br><b>Phone Version Instructions:</b><p>When you visit the Guide URL, we detect your browser and render the Guide in a manner that is optimized for your device type and size.  On the Apple iOS and Android supported phone form factor, the guide will look like the screen shown below, after you accept the Terms & Conditions upon your first visit.<p><img src="images/ph1.PNG" width="25%"/><p>From the INDEX view, you can toggle the REFERENCES button to view the REFERENCES section of the GUIDE.  Tapping HOME from this view you can view Nestle contact information and you can tap any of the links to leave the Guide and visit the associated site on the web or Facebook.  Additionally, from the phone, you can tap to dial any of the listed numbers.  Tapping INDEX from this view will return you to the PRODUCT INDEX again.<p><img src="images/ph_refs_1.png" width="25%"/><img src="images/ph_refs_3.png" width="25%"/><img src="images/ph_refs_2.png" width="25%"/><p>Once back at the INDEX, you can tap the CATEGORIES icon to bring up a picker-wheel which will allow you to move the wheel up and down to find the Category or Sub-category you wish and then press DONE to return to and sort the INDEX.  The Categories are shown in a larger font and the Sub-Categories in a smaller font, but the groups are color-coded.   As an example, shown below, the main Category is \u2018Pediatric\u2019 is in blue, but the sub-categories belonging to \u2018Pediatric\u2019 are all blue as well.<p><img src="images/ph3.PNG" width="25%"/><p><p>To reset the INDEX at any time, simply open CATEGORIES, and return to \u2018Show All Products\u2019 at the top and press DONE, as shown below:<p><img src="images/ph4.PNG" width="25%"/><p>Additionally, when in the uncategorized INDEX view, you can refine the index to only include products by a particular BRAND name by tapping the BRAND SEARCH field.  The example in below shows the letters \u2018B\u2019 and \u2018o\u2019 entered into the filed which eliminates anything not a \u201cBoost\u201d product.  You can reset the index by tapping on the field and trying another query that matches a Brand in the guide or clearing the field.<p><img src="images/ph5.PNG" width="25%"/><p>From the INDEX view, you can use your finger to scroll through the index to find any Product by name you wish.    Once you tap on the Product, you will be taken to the ABOUT view as shown below:<p><img src="images/ph6.PNG" width="25%"/><p>On the ABOUT view, you will see the highlights at a glance.  You can return to the INDEX view at any time by pressing the INDEX back button at the top left of the Product view.  Additional views with more detailed information are available by clicking on the related icon on the bottom of the screen.  These include FEATURES for Features and Uses, INGREDIENTS for a list of ingredients, NUTRITION for Nutrition Information, and ORDERING for ordering information.  Certain Products are available to recommend via email, and when this is available, you will see the \u2018MAIL\u2019 envelope icon at the top right of the Product Name label.  By tapping the MAIL icon, you will invoke your locally installed email client as shown below.  (Please note, you must have a local email client configured for use prior to using this feature.)<p><img src="images/ph7.PNG" width="25%"/><p>Using the icons at the bottom of the screen will navigate between the views shown in the various examples shown below.  You can scroll down to reveal additional information in the different views when applicable.<p><img src="images/ph8.PNG" width="25%"/><p>The above image shows the FEATURES view, this give the user an overview of all the FEATURES & USES of the Nestl\u00e9 Product shown in the Title Bar.<p><img src="images/ph9.PNG" width="25%"/><p>The above image shows the INGREDIENTS view, which gives the full list of INGREDIENTS for the product, a user can scroll down to see more if they fall off the screen.<p><img src="images/ph10.PNG" width="25%"/><p>The above image shows the NUTRITION view, which has the NUTRITION TABLE associated with the product.  More detail is available by scrolling down on very long tables.<p><img src="images/ph11.PNG" width="25%"/><p>The above image shows the ORDERING view, which has the packaging types as well as UPC\u2019s for the associated product.  From this view (on any product) a user can tap the ADDITIONAL ORDERING INFO button to receive a large table of all supplemental ordering information.<p><b>Creating a shortcut on the iPhone</b><p>A user can add a short cut to their iOS device desktop by simply pressing the SHORTCUT icon in the middle of their browser toolbar at the bottom of their screen and tapping the \u201cAdd to Home Screen\u201d button and then tapping \u201cAdd\u201d as shown below.<p><img src="images/ph12.PNG" width="25%"/><img src="images/ph13.PNG" width="25%"/><p>When you launch the Guide from your iPhone\'s springboard, you will see a loading indicator while the Guide application is refreshed to ensure timely and up-to-date information.<p><img src="images/ph14.PNG" width="25%"/><img src="images/ph15.PNG" width="25%"/><p><br><b>Creating a shortcut on an Android device</b><p>Once you have loaded the Product Guide, tap the \'SETTINGS\' hard button on your Android Phone.<p>Choose "More" from the settings option.<p>Click "Add Bookmark"<p><img src="images/aph1.jpeg" width="25%"/><p>Click "OK" to save the bookmark.<p>Once back on your Home-screen, find a free spot and press on the screen and hold until the "Add to Home screen" shows up.<p>Choose "Shortcuts".<p><img src="images/aph2.jpeg" width="25%"/><p>Choose "Bookmark".<p><img src="images/aph3.jpeg" width="25%"/><p>Finally, choose the recently created bookmark for the Product Guide.<p> </div><br/><br/><div id="compatibility" class=landing_html><h1>Nestle HealthCare Nutrition Product GuideCompatibility Information</h1><p>This web site is a special web application that is designed to take advantage of your smartphone, tablet, or Chrome or Safari browser on your desktop.  To find out if your device or browser is supported, please use the methods described below. <br> (Note: a user must be running a plain installation of an Android or Safari Web-kit based browser. We do not support Opera on iOS or Android, or custom installations of browsers from the Apple iTunes Store or Android Marketplace such as Firefox.  There are also reports of incompatibility with custom browsers such as the one used in customized Android builds seen on HTC devices.)<p><b>ANDROID</b><p>On your smartphone (such as those made by Motorola and Samsung) you must be running at least version 2.2.x or 2.3.x running on the phone factor.  To check which version you are running follow these easy steps:<p>1.\tFrom the \u2018Home\u2019 screen, press the \u2018Menu\u2019 hard key to display the \u2018Settings\u2019 soft key.<br>2.  Inside \u201cSettings\u201d select the \u201cAbout phone\u201d option found towards the bottom of the list.<br>3.  Now look for the \u201cAndroid version\u201d field to see what version your phone has.  If it has a number beginning with 2.2 or 2.3, then your phone is compatible with the application.  (Note, you may want to tap on the \u201cSystem Updates\u201d option to see if a newer version of Android is available for your device.)<br><p>We also support the Android tablets running a specific version of Android nicknamed \u201cHoneycomb\u201d, but is actually version 3.0.  You can find this on your table in the exact same manner as above, but you will see either version 3.0, 3.1, or 3.2 depending on the device you are running.  Please note, tablets running 2.x version of Android are not specifically supported, but may run the Phone version of the application.<br><p><b>APPLE iOS</b><p>Additionally, we fully support iOS based operating system devices such as the iPhone 4 and iPhone 3GS as well as Apple tablets like the iPad 1 and 2.  In order to run the web application in the device browser, you must be running at least version 4 of the iOS operating system.  To see what version you have, you can follow these steps on either device:<p>1.\tLocate the \u2018Settings\u2019 app on your device, and scroll down to the \u2018General\u2019 option entry.<br>2.\tChoose the \u2018About\u2019 option at the top of the list.<br>3.\tScroll down until you see the \u2018Version\u2019 entry, this displays the numeric version of iOS you are running.  For the iPad and iPhone (or iPod Touch), you must be running a firmware that begins with the number 4, such as 4.3.2.  Updates are available by connecting your device to iTunes where you will be notified if a newer firmware is available. <br><p><b>WINDOWS</b><p>Our web application also supports the following web browsers running on windows and can be found at the following links:<p>Chrome 14+<br>http://www.google.com/chrome<p>Safari 5+<br>http://www.apple.com/safari/download/<p><b>MAC OS X</b><p>Finally, our web application also supports the following web browsers running on the latest version of MAC OS X and can be found at the following links:<p>Chrome 14+<br>http://www.google.com/chrome<p>Safari 5+<br>http://www.apple.com/safari/download/<p></div>';
